  "statement": {
    "portrait": "images/kremenskii.png",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Vulnerability and the absence of resistance expose the underlying dynamics of social relations. When dependency arises, people often reveal their true nature; without resistance, their actions rest entirely on the conscience of society.",
      "My practice translates these dynamics into material form. By compressing and deforming substances such as gravel—incapable of resistance—I produce traces that register force and dependency. These imprints act as evidence of power relations and as memory of the mechanisms shaping human interaction."
    ],
    "exhibitions": [
      { "year": "2024", "event": "Im contrast, Elsiens Art Gallery, Stuttgart" },
      { "year": "2023", "event": "Material Traces, Elsiens Art Gallery, Stuttgart" }
    ],
    "pressKitPdf": "files/press-kit.pdf"
  },

